NAME
    bandwhich - Display current network utilization by process, connection and remote IP/hostname

SYNOPSIS
    bandwhich [OPTIONS]

DESCRIPTION
    bandwhich is a CLI utility for displaying current network utilization by process, connection and remote IP/hostname. It provides a real-time view of which processes are using the network, and how much bandwidth they're using.

OPTIONS
    -h, --help                   Prints help information
    -V, --version                Prints version information
    -i, --interface <interface>  The network interface to listen on
    -n, --no-resolve             Do not attempt to resolve IPs to host names
    -r, --raw                    Machine-friendly output (CSV)
    -s, --show-dns               Show DNS queries
    -t, --total-utilization      Show total network utilization
    --no-cache                   Disable caching of resolved hostnames
    -c, --connections            Show connections
    -p, --processes              Show processes
    -d, --dns                    Show DNS queries

USAGE
    sudo bandwhich [OPTIONS]

EXAMPLES
    sudo bandwhich
    sudo bandwhich -i eth0
    sudo bandwhich --raw

OUTPUT
    By default, bandwhich displays a real-time, formatted table showing network usage by process, connection, and remote IP/hostname.
